OL,3,GStrathclyde
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FAll parts will have a dry day
OL,6,Fwith variable amounts of cloud. Some
OL,7,Fsunny intervals, the best of the
OL,8,Fsunshine across Argyll. Warm in the
OL,9,Fbrighter west.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FThis evening will be dry with
OL,12,Fsome late sunshine. Then it will
OL,13,Fmainly dry with clear periods, the odd
OL,14,Fshower possible in the south later. A
OL,15,Fwarm night in west.
OL,16,
OL,17,CThursday:FAll parts will have a dry
OL,18,Fday with plenty of sunshine. Becoming
OL,19,Fvery warm, locally hot. Chance of a
OL,20,Fshower along the west coast late
OL,21,Fevening.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
